  content `[Act to have overriding effect.]--- Omitted by the Waqf (Amendment) Act, 2025 (14 of 2025), s. 45 (w.e.f. 08-04-2025).`
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_108_a_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_44_74_00001_199543_1517807323904&sectionId=29473&sectionno=108A&orderno=120&orgactid=AC_CEN_44_74_00001_199543_1517807323904
obj_root_law_sections_108_a_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_108_b:
  sectionId (95768)
  sectionNo 108B
  orderNo 121
  title `Power of Central Government to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_108_b_content
  footnotes `1 Ins. by Act 14 of 2025, s. 46, (w.e.f. 08-04-2025).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_44_74_00001_199543_1517807323904&sectionId=95768&sectionno=108B&orderno=121&orgactid=AC_CEN_44_74_00001_199543_1517807323904
obj_root_law_sections_108_b_content:
  string
  line `^1[108B. Power of Central Government to make rules.--- (1) The Central Government may, by`
  line `notification in the Official Gazette, make rules to carry out the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing powers, the Central`
  line `Government may make rules for all or any of the following matters, namely:---`
  line
  line `(a) the waqf asset management system for the registration, accounts, audit and other details of`
  line `waqf and Board under clause (ka), and the manner of payments for maintenance of widow, divorced`
  line `woman and orphan under sub-clause (iv) of clause (r), of section 3;`
  line
  line `(b) any other particulars under clause (j) of sub-section (2) of section 3B;`
  line
  line `(c) the manner in which details of waqf to be uploaded under sub-section (2B) of section 5;`
  line
  line `(d) any other particulars under clause (f) of sub-section (3) of section 36;`
  line
  line `(e) the manner in which the Board shall maintain the register of auqaf under sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 37;`
  line
  line `(f) such other particulars to be contained in the register of auqaf under clause (f) of sub-section (1)`
  line `of section 37;`
  line
  line `(g) form and manner and particulars of the statement of accounts under sub-section (2) of`
  line `section 46;`
  line
  line `(h) the manner for publishing audit report under sub-section (2A) of section 47;`
  line
  line `(i) the manner of publication of proceedings and orders of Board under sub-section (2A) of`
  line `section 48;`
  line
  line `(j) any other matter which is required to be, or may be, prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) Every rule made by the Central Government under this Act shall be laid, as soon as may be after it`
  line `is made, before each House of Parliament, while it is in session, for a total period of thirty days which`
  line `may be comprised in one session or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the`
  line `session immediately following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in`
  line `making any modification in the rule or both Houses agree that the rule should not be made, the rule shall`
  line `thereafter have effect only in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that`
  line `any such modification or annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done`
  line `under that rule.]`
obj_root_law_sections_109:
  sectionId (29474)
  sectionNo (109)
  orderNo 122
  title `Power to make rules`
  content obj_root_law_sections_109_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_109_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_44_74_00001_199543_1517807323904&sectionId=29474&sectionno=109&orderno=122&orgactid=AC_CEN_44_74_00001_199543_1517807323904
obj_root_law_sections_109_content:
  string
  line `(1) The State Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette,`
  line `make rules to carry out the purposes of this Act, other than those of Chapter III.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing powers, such rules may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:---`
  line
  line `^1[(i) the qualifications required to be fulfilled by a person to be appointed as a mutawalli under`
  line `clause (i) of section 3;`
  line
  line `^2* * * * *]`
  line
  line `(ii) any other matter under clause (f) of sub-section (4) of section 4;`
  line
  line `(iii) the particulars which a list of ^3[Auqaf] published under sub-section (2) of section 5, may`
  line contain;
  line
  line `^4* * * * *`
  line
  line `(v) the terms and conditions of service of the Chief Executive Officer under sub-section (2) of`
  line `section 23;`
  line
  line `(vi) the conditions and restrictions subject to which the Chief Executive Officer or any other`
  line `officer may inspect any public office, records or registers ^5[under sub-section (1) of] section 29;`
  line
  line `^6[(via) the period within which the mutawalli or any other person may produce documents related`
  line `to waqf properties under sub-section (2) of ^7[section 29];`
  line
  line `(vib) the conditions under which an agency of the Government or any other organisation may`
  line `supply copies of records, registers and other documents under sub-section (3) of ^7[section 29];]`
  line
  line `(vii) the conditions subject to which an Executive Officer and supporting staff may be appointed`
  line `under sub-section (1) of section 38;`
  line
  line `(viii) the manner in which an inquiry may be held by the Chief Executive Officer under`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 39;`
  line
  line `(ix) the form in which, and the time within which, a separate budget for ^3[Auqaf] under the direct`
  line `management of the Board shall be prepared under sub-section (1) of section 45;`
  line
  line `(x) the interval at which accounts of ^3[Auqaf] may be audited in pursuance of the provisions of`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 47;`
  line
  line `^8* * * * *`
  line
  line `(xii) the guidance subject to which the Collector shall recover the property transferred in`
  line `contravention of the provisions of this Act, under section 52;`
  line
  line `(xiii) the manner of service of notice issued under sub-section (1) of section 54 and the manner in`
  line `which any inquiry is to be made under sub-section (3) of that section;`
  line
  line `(xiv) the manner in which any inquiry may be held under section 64 or section 71;`
  line
  line `(xv) the other matters which may be specified in the report submitted under sub-section (3) of`
  line `section 65;`
  line
  line `(xvi) the manner of publication of order made under sub-section (2) of section 67;`
  line
  line `(xvii) the manner in which consultation may be made with mutawalli under sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 69;`
  line
  line `(xviii) the manner of publication of order made under sub-section (3) of section 69;`
  line
  line `^9[(xviiia) the manner of giving notice inviting objections under proviso to sub-section (4) of`
  line `section 69;]`
  line
  line `(xix) the rate at which contribution is to be made by a mutawalli under section 72;`
  line
  line `(xx) the payment of moneys into the ^10[Waqf] Fund, the investment, the custody and disbursement`
  line `of such moneys under section 77;`
  line
  line `(xxi) the form in which, and the time within which, the budget of the Board may be prepared and`
  line `submitted under section 78;`
  line
  line `(xxii) the time within which application is to be made to the Tribunal under sub-section (2) of`
  line `section 83;`
  line
  line `^11(xxiia) the terms and conditions of appointment including the salaries and allowances payable to`
  line `the Chairman and other members other than persons appointed as ex officio members under`
  line `sub-section (4A) of section 83;]`
  line
  line `(xxiii) the procedure which the Tribunal shall follow under sub-section (6) of section 83;`
  line
  line `(xxiv) the form in which the annual report is to be submitted and the matters which such report`
  line `shall contain under section 98; and`
  line
  line `(xxv) any other matter which is required to be, or may be, prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_109_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 27 of 2013, s. 57, for cl. (i) (w.e.f. 01-11-2013).`
  line
  line `2. Cl. (ia) omitted by Act 14 of 2025, s. 47 (w.e.f. 08-04-2025).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 27 of 2013, s. 4, for "Wakfs" (w.e.f. 01-11-2013).`
  line
  line `4. Cl. (iv) omitted by Act 14 of 2025, s. 47 (w.e.f. 08-04-2025).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by Act 27 of 2013, s. 57, for "under" (w.e.f. 01-11-2013).`
  line
  line `6. Ins. by Act 27 of 2013, s. 57 (w.e.f. 01-11-2013).`
  line
  line `7. Subs. by Act 14 of 2025, s. 47, for "section 31" (w.e.f. 08-04-2025).`
  line
  line `8. Cl. (xi) omitted by Act 27 of 2013, s. 57, (w.e.f. 01-11-2013).`
  line
  line `9. Ins. by Act 14 of 2025, s. 47 (w.e.f. 08-04-2025).`
  line
  line `10. Subs. by Act 27 of 2013, s. 4, for "wakf" (w.e.f. 01-11-2013).`
  line
  line `11. Ins. by s. 57,ibid.. (w.e.f. 01-11-2013).`
obj_root_law_sections_110:
  sectionId (29475)
  sectionNo (110)
  orderNo 123
  title `Powers to make regulations by the Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_110_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_110_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_44_74_00001_199543_1517807323904&sectionId=29475&sectionno=110&orderno=123&orgactid=AC_CEN_44_74_00001_199543_1517807323904
obj_root_law_sections_110_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Board may, with previous sanction of the`
  line `State Government, make regulations not inconsistent with this Act or the rules made thereunder, for`
  line `carrying out its functions under this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing powers, such regulations`
  line `may provide for all or any of the following matters, namely--`
  line
  line `(a) the time and places of the meetings of the Board under sub-section (1) of section 17;`
  line
  line `(b) the procedure and conduct of business at the meetings of the Board;`
  line
  line `(c) the constitution and functions of the committees and the Board and the procedure for`
  line `transaction of business at the meetings of such committees;`
  line
  line `(d) the allowances or fees to be paid to the Chairperson or members of the Board or members of`
  line committees;
  line
  line `(e) the terms and conditions of service of the officers and other employees of the Board`
  line `under sub-section (2) of section 24;`
  line
  line `^1* * * * *`
  line
  line `(h) the form in which, and the time within which, the budgets of ^2[Auqaf] may be prepared and`
  line `submitted by the Mutawalli and approved by the Board under sub-section (1) of section 44;`
  line
  line `(i) the books of accounts and other books to be maintained by the Board under section 79;`
  line
  line `(j) fees payable for inspection of proceedings and records of the Board or for issue of copies of`
  line `the same;`
  line
  line `(k) persons by whom any order or decision of the Board may be authenticated; and`
  line
  line `(l) any other matter which has to be, or may be, provided by regulations.`
  line
  line `(3) All regulations made under this section shall be published in the Official Gazette and shall have`
  line `effect from the date of such publication.`
obj_root_law_sections_110_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Cls. (f) and (g) omitted by Act 14 of 2025, s. 48 (w.e.f. 08-04-2025).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 27 of 2013, s. 4, for "wakfs" (w.e.f. 1-11-2013).`
obj_root_law_sections_111:
  sectionId (29476)
  sectionNo (111)
  orderNo 124
  title `Laying of rules and regulations before State Legislature`
  content obj_root_law_sections_111_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_111_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_44_74_00001_199543_1517807323904&sectionId=29476&sectionno=111&orderno=124&orgactid=AC_CEN_44_74_00001_199543_1517807323904
obj_root_law_sections_111_content:
  string
  line `Every rule made under section`
  line `109 and every regulation made under section 110 shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made, before`
  line `the State Legislature.`
obj_root_law_sections_111_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_112:
  sectionId (29477)
  sectionNo (112)
  orderNo 125
  title `Repeal and savings`
  content obj_root_law_sections_112_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_112_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_44_74_00001_199543_1517807323904&sectionId=29477&sectionno=112&orderno=125&orgactid=AC_CEN_44_74_00001_199543_1517807323904
obj_root_law_sections_112_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Wakf Act, 1954 (29 of 1954) and the Wakf (Amendment)`
  line `Act, 1984 (69 of 1984) are hereby repealed.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding such repeal, anything done or any action taken under the said Acts shall be`
  line `deemed to have been done or taken under the corresponding provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(3) If, immediately before the commencement of this Act, in any State, there is in force in that State,`
  line `any law which corresponds to this Act that corresponding law shall stand repealed:`
  line
  line `Provided that such repeal shall not affect the previous operation of that corresponding law, and`
  line `subject thereto, anything done or any action taken in the exercise of any power conferred by or under the`
  line `corresponding law shall be deemed to have been done or taken in the exercise of the powers conferred by`
  line `or under this Act as if this Act was in force on the day on which such things were done or action was`
  line taken.
obj_root_law_sections_112_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_113:
  sectionId (29478)
  sectionNo (113)
  orderNo 126
  title `Power to remove difficulties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_113_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_113_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_44_74_00001_199543_1517807323904&sectionId=29478&sectionno=113&orderno=126&orgactid=AC_CEN_44_74_00001_199543_1517807323904
obj_root_law_sections_113_content:
  string
  line `(1) If any difficulty arises in giving effect to the provisions of`
  line `this Act, the Central Government may, by order, not inconsistent with the provisions of this Act, remove`
  line `the difficulty:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such order shall be made after the expiry of the period of two years from the`
  line `commencement of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) However, order made under this section shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made, before`
  line `each House of Parliament.`
obj_root_law_sections_113_footnotes:
  string
  line
